com.cerner.bunsen.codes

Class ValueSets

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cerner.bunsen.codes.ValueSets

  • public class ValueSets
extends Object
    An immutable collection of FHIR ValueSets. This class is used to import value set content, explore it, and persist it to a database.

      • getValueSets

        public org.apache.spark.sql.Dataset<org.hl7.fhir.dstu3.model.ValueSet> getValueSets()
        Returns a dataset of value sets to inspect metadata. Since the value sets themselves can be quite large, the values in this dataset do not contain them. Instead, users should use the getValues() method to query values in depth.
        Returns:
        a dataset of value sets that do not contain concept values.

      • withValueSetsFromDirectory

        public ValueSets withValueSetsFromDirectory(String path)
        Reads all value sets from a given directory and adds them to our collection. The directory may be anything readable from a Spark path, including local filesystems, HDFS, S3, or others.
        Parameters:
        path - a path from which value sets will be loaded
        Returns:
        an instance of ValueSets that includes the contents from that directory.

      • withDisjointValueSetsFromDirectory

        public ValueSets withDisjointValueSetsFromDirectory(String path)
        Returns all value sets that are disjoint with value sets stored in the default database and adds them to our collection. The directory may be anything readable from a Spark path, including local filesystems, HDFS, S3, or others.
        Parameters:
        path - a path from which disjoint value sets will be loaded
        Returns:
        an instance of ValueSets that includes content from that directory that is disjoint with content already contained in the default database.

      • withDisjointValueSetsFromDirectory

        Parameters:
        path - a path from which disjoint value sets will be loaded
        database - the database to check value sets against
        Returns:
        an instance of ValueSets that includes content from that directory that is disjoint with content already contained in the given database.

      • writeToTables

        public void writeToTables(String valuesTable,
                          String valueSetTable)
        Writes value sets to the given tables.

        Warning: these updates are likely not atomic due to the lack of transactional semantics in the underlying data store. Concurrent users may see previous items removed before new ones are added, or items appear separately than others. This is intended for use in a user-specific sandbox or staging environment.

        Parameters:
        valuesTable - name of the table to which the value records are saved
        valueSetTable - name of the table to which the value set metadata is saved
